The OTel plugin is a `Plugin<Project>`, not a `Plugin<Settings>`. It needs to be applied in `build.gradle.kts`, not `settings.gradle.kts`.

Update your sample project's config:

**`settings.gradle.kts`** -- only the Tuist plugin:
```kotlin
plugins {
    id("dev.tuist") version "..."
}

tuist {
    url = "http://localhost:8080"
    project = "your-account/your-project"
}
```

**`build.gradle.kts`** (root project) -- add the OTel plugin here:
```kotlin
plugins {
    id("com.atkinsondev.opentelemetry-build") version "4.6.2"
}
```

The Tuist plugin's auto-configuration uses `project.plugins.withId("com.atkinsondev.opentelemetry-build")`, which fires when the plugin is applied at the project level. So it will detect and configure it automatically from there.
